Charles,<br><br>
Your paradox sounds pretty good until you take into account that we supported the Diem regime which was responsible for its own brutality, repression, thievery and general corruption.<br><br>
Madame Nhu who was the sister-in-law of Diem said, when Buddhist monks were immolating themselves, that she would gladly furnish the matches.<br><br>
Diem represented the type of freedom which gave him and his cronies license to steal and make huge profits at the expense of the people they purported to represent.<br><br>
Diem was not President of South Vietnam because of the &quot;will of the governed&quot;.
